Police confiscated six unlicensed firearms and a stolen vehicle they were using to commit crime. JOHANNESBURG - Six suspected robbers have arrested in Tembisa after the police received a tip-off that they were on the mission to rob a business on Saturday morning.Police confiscated six unlicensed firearms and a stolen vehicle they were using to commit crime.Authorities say they are profiling the suspects and they might be linked to other criminal activities.Spokesperson Kay Makhubele explains: The vehicle used was stolen in Gauteng. They will be charged for being in possession of illegal firearms and a stolen vehicle. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)